Consider a random vector $X=[X_1, X_2, \ldots , X_n]$ where $X_i$ ($i \in 1, 2,\ldots, n$) are independent complex Gaussian random variables with zero mean and variance $\sigma_i^2$, i.e.,  $X_i \sim CN(0, \sigma_i^2)$. How can I find expectation of norm of $X$, where the norm of $X$ is given by 
  \begin{equation}
\|X\|=\sqrt{\sum_{i=1}^n |X_i|^2}
\end{equation} Any help regarding this problem is really appreciated. Thanks.

